<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="459" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,823,1173]" pageId="1" pageNumber="459">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,967,992]" pageId="1" pageNumber="459">Remarks.</emphasis>
The redescriptions and comments about this species can be found in the papers of 
<bibRefCitation author="Zwick" box="[1282,1432,967,992]" pageId="1" pageNumber="459" refString="Zwick, P. (1972) Die Plecopteren Pictets und Burmeisters, mit Angaben uber weitere Arten (Insecta). Revue Suisse de Zoologie, 78 (4), 1123 - 1194." type="journal article" year="1972">Zwick (1972</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Zwick" box="[151,210,1004,1028]" pageId="1" pageNumber="459" refString="Zwick, P. (1973) Die Plecopteren-Arten Enderleins (Insecta): Revision der Typen. Annales Zoologici Warszawa, 30 (16), 471 - 507." type="journal article" year="1973">1973</bibRefCitation>
), 
<bibRefCitation author="Froehlich" box="[230,419,1004,1029]" pageId="1" pageNumber="459" refString="Froehlich, C. G. (2002) Anacroneuria mainly from southern Brazil and northeastern Argentina (Plecoptera: Perlidae). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 115 (1), 75 - 107." type="journal article" year="2002">
Froehlich (
<number box="[351,410,1004,1028]" pageId="1" pageNumber="459" value="2002.0">2002</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation box="[472,694,1004,1029]" pageId="1" pageNumber="459" refString="Baldin, C., Bispo, P. C. &amp; Novaes, M. C. (2013) New species and records of Anacroneuria (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from Rio de Janeiro State, Brazil. Zootaxa, 3694 (4), 391 - 397. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3694.4.7" type="journal article">
Baldin 
<emphasis box="[554,610,1004,1028]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="459">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[624,685,1004,1028]" pageId="1" pageNumber="459" value="2013.0">2013</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. The adult males studied here have a forewing length of 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.16" metricValueMax="1.21" metricValueMin="1.1099999999999999" pageId="1" pageNumber="459" unit="mm" value="11.6" valueMax="12.1" valueMin="11.1">11.1–12.1 mm</quantity>
. The structure of the penial armature (
<figureCitation box="[627,734,1039,1064]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1906,1929]" captionTargetBox="[157,1433,201,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Anacroneuria debilis. Male: (1) head and pronotum; (2) sternum 9; (3 – 5) penial armature (3 dorsal, 4 ventral and 5 lateral views). Scales: figure (1) 0.5 mm; figure (2) 1.0 mm; figures (3 – 5) 0.75 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="459">
Figs. 
<number box="[690,734,1039,1064]" pageId="1" pageNumber="459" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5</number>
</figureCitation>
) agrees with 
<bibRefCitation author="Zwick" box="[885,1038,1039,1064]" pageId="1" pageNumber="459" refString="Zwick, P. (1972) Die Plecopteren Pictets und Burmeisters, mit Angaben uber weitere Arten (Insecta). Revue Suisse de Zoologie, 78 (4), 1123 - 1194." type="journal article" year="1972">
Zwick (
<number box="[972,1030,1040,1064]" pageId="1" pageNumber="459" value="1972.0">1972</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation box="[1093,1316,1039,1064]" pageId="1" pageNumber="459" refString="Baldin, C., Bispo, P. C. &amp; Novaes, M. C. (2013) New species and records of Anacroneuria (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from Rio de Janeiro State, Brazil. Zootaxa, 3694 (4), 391 - 397. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3694.4.7" type="journal article">
Baldin 
<emphasis box="[1175,1232,1040,1064]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="459">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[1247,1309,1040,1064]" pageId="1" pageNumber="459" value="2013.0">2013</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. However, in several of the above listed males, the penial armature is slightly smaller and has a stronger dorsal inclination apically. The penial differences at this time are accepted as variation occurring in 
<taxonomicName box="[1099,1208,1112,1136]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="debilis">
<emphasis box="[1099,1208,1112,1136]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="459">A. debilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, study of additional material from different localities is needed to ascertain if cryptic species are involved.
</paragraph>
